article.headline: Arkansas State 80, Centenary 69
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. (AP) -- J.J. Montgomery scored 20 points and pulled down nine rebounds Saturday night as Arkansas State opened its season with an 80-69 win over Centenary. The Indians (1-0) used a 16-2 run midway through the second half to seal the victory ASU led 40-33 at the half. Dewarick Spencer chipped in 17 points and Isaac Wells pumped in 15 points and also hauled in nine boards for the Indians. But the big rebounder for ASU was Kitus Witherspoon, with 15 rebounds in just 23 minutes of play. ASU built the lead to 51-41 in first 5:02 of the second half. Spencer then stole the ball from Centenary's Chad Maclies and was all alone for a monstrous dunk to put the Tribe up 12 with 14:34 left in the game. Maclies led Centenary (0-1) with 16 points and 11 rebounds. Jarmorrow Moragne added 13 points for the visitors and Cody Hopkins came off the bench to score 11.
